The article is a statement by the President on the passing of Tom Menino, the former mayor of Boston. The President describes Menino as bold, big-hearted, and Boston strong, and praises his leadership in making Boston a vibrant and world-class city. The President also mentions Menino's contributions to revitalizing neighborhoods, improving schools, and making communities safer. He expresses his condolences to Menino's wife, Angela, and the entire Menino family, as well as the people of Boston who loved and were loved by Menino.